body:
* Render Details column in plan table if connected against 4.1 database
* Keep one bookmark per database.
Support for neo4j+s, neo4j+ssc, bolt+s, and bolt+ssc
Fix bug with running interactively on a database where a password change was required
- Fix bug with setting initial password interactively
- Fix bug when accessing a database with auth disabled

Cypher shell 1.1.9:
 
- Bug fix: Always said `0 rows available`
- Bug fix: Removed unnecessary new lines
A few bug fixes in this release

name: 1.0.0-RC1
body:
### Bug fixes
- Fixed lack of interactive detection on Windows [#57](https://github.com/neo4j/cypher-shell/pull/57)
  - Now always uses interactive mode on Windows by default
  - If non-interactive mode is desired (for scripting) then a new flag `--non-interactive` has been added

### Enhancements
- Added modes: verbose/plain. Verbose displays more information and is intended for interactive use. Plain displays only the data from queries, intended for scripting [#23](https://github.com/neo4j/cypher-shell/pull/23)
- Added multiline statement support [#25](https://github.com/neo4j/cypher-shell/pull/25)
- Added option (`--encryption`) to choose between encrypted and unencrypted communication with the server [#36](https://github.com/neo4j/cypher-shell/pull/36)
- Added option `--debug` to get additional information in case of errors [#41](https://github.com/neo4j/cypher-shell/pull/41)
- Made semicolons optional for shell commands [#55](https://github.com/neo4j/cypher-shell/pull/55)
- Added version of connected Neo4j to welcome message [#56](https://github.com/neo4j/cypher-shell/pull/56)
